quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  27,82,"And when the word is fulfiled against them We will bring forth a beast out of the earth (gross materialism?) that shall speak to (or wound) them, because mankind had not faith in Our revelations"
  27,83,"And the Day when We will gather from every nation a troop of those who denied our revelations, and they shall be marshalled"
  27,84,"Until, when they come before their Lord, He will say, \"Did you deny my revelations when you had compassed no knowledge thereof? Or what is it that you were doing"
  27,85,"And the Word shall be fulfiled concerning them because they did wrong, and they will not be able to speak"
  27,86,"Did they not see that how We have made the night for them to rest in, and the day to see by? Verily, in that are signs to people who believe"
  27,87,"And the Day when the trumpet shall be blown and all who are in the heavens and the earth shall be startled in fear (or horrified), save whom Allah wills. And all shall come unto Him, humbled"
  27,88,"And you see the mountains (things seemingly firm and reliable) which you do deem firm, drifting away like the passing of the clouds - the work of Allah who orders all things. Verily, He is well aware of what you do"
  27,89,He who brings a good deed shall have better than its worth; and from the alarm of that day they shall be safe
  27,90,But those who bring an evil deed shall be thrown down upon their faces in the Fire. Shall you be rewarded save for what you did
  27,91,"(Say) I (Muhammad) am commanded to serve the Lord of this land (Mecca) which He has made sacred, and unto Whom belong all things. And I am commanded to be of those who Surrender (unto Him)"
  27,92,"And to recite the Quran; And he who is guided right, is guided right only for his own soul; and as for him who goes astray - say unto him, \"I am only of those who warn"
  27,93,"And say, \"Praise be to Allah, Who will show you His signs so that you shall recognize them; for your Lord is not heedless of what you do"
  28,1,TA SIN MIM
  28,2,These are the verses of the Book (Scripture) that clarifies
  28,3,We narrate unto you something from the history of Moses and Pharaoh with truth unto a people who believe
  28,4,"Verily, Pharaoh exalted himself in the land and divided the people thereof into sects (and casts); one section of them he oppressed, slaughtering their sons and sparing their women. Verily, he was of those who work corruption"
  28,5,"And We wished to be gracious to those who were weakened by oppression in the earth, and to make them models, and to make them the inheritors"
  28,6,And to establish them firmly in the earth; and to show Pharaoh and Haman and their hosts that which they feared from them
  28,7,"And We inspired the mother of Moses, saying, \"Suckle him; and when you are afraid for him then float him into the river, and fear not and grieve not; verily, We shall restore him to you, and make him of one of Our Messengers"
  28,8,"And Pharaoh´s family picked him up that he might become for them a foe and a grief; for verily, Pharaoh and Haman and their hosts were ever sinners"
  28,9,"And Pharaoh´s wife said, \"He is a joy to my eyes, and to yours. Kill him not; it may be that he will profit us, or that we may take him for a son;\" for they perceived not"
  28,10,"And the heart of the mother of Moses became void (empty) on the morrow; she well nigh disclosed him, had We not strengthened her heart that she might be of the believers"
  28,11,"And she said to his (Moses´) sister, \"Follow him up.\" And she (his sister) watched him from afar (or as a stranger), and they perceive not"